deration%20changes.%3Cp%3ERichard%20Bord%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMeta%20said%20Tuesday%20it%20plans%20to%20drop%20third-party%20fact-checkers%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20community%20notes%20feature.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeta%20CMO%20Alex%20Schultz%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20election%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20the%20presidency%20influenced%20the%20shift.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20also%20said%20a%20change%20in%20how%20Americans%20view%20censorship%20and%20content%20moderation%20played%20a%20role.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20it%20was%20ditching%20fact%20checkers%2C%20Alex%20Schultz%2C%20the%20company's%20chief%20marketing%20officer%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20election%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20as%20president%20influenced%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLook%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20adjust%20to%20any%20administration%20and%20we%20always%20do%20and%20that%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20appropriate%2C%26quot%3B%20Schultz%20said%20at%20CES%202025%20in%20Las%20Vegas%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWe've%20worked%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration%20through%20its%20term.%20We'll%20work%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20through%20its%20term.%20Elections%20have%20consequences.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Meta%20announced%20it%20would%20stop%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-community-notes-third-party-fact-checkers-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird-party%20fact-checkers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20favor%20of%20user-generated%20community%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20said%20it%20was%20moving%20some%20of%20its%20content%20moderation%20teams%20from%20California%2C%20which%20typically%20votes%20Democratic%2C%20to%20Texas%2C%20which%20typically%20votes%20Republican.%20Meta%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20move%20would%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20remove%20the%20concern%20that%20biased%20employees%20are%20overly%20censoring%20content.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20added%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20incoming%20administration%20playing%20a%20role%2C%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20decision%20was%20also%20influenced%20by%20a%20shift%20in%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vibes%20in%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20said%20there's%20a%20change%20in%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-zuckerberg-content-moderation-california-texas-censorship-bias-musk-x-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%20broadly%20view%20censorship%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20free%20speech%2C%20and%20content%20moderation%2C%20which%20he%20said%20was%20signaled%20by%20the%20results%20of%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20big%2C%20big%20shift%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%2C%20yeah%2C%20we're%20responding%20to%20that%20at%20this%20time%20because%20that's%20the%20logical%20time%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20said%20the%20new%20community%20notes%20feature%20would%20be%20similar%20to%20the%20one%20used%20on%20Elon%20Musk's%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20which%20allows%20users%20to%20add%20notes%20to%20posts%20that%20potentially%20contain%20misinformation%20or%20are%20missing%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20told%20BI%20the%20announced%20changes%20also%20bring%20Zuckerberg%20%26quot%3Bback%20to%20the%20core%20of%20what%20he%20cares%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20fundamentally%20he's%20been%20pushed%20into%20a%20place%20that%20was%20further%20than%20he%20wanted%20to%20be%20in%20terms%20of%20censorship%20and%20in%20content%20moderation%2C%26quot%3B%20Schultz%20said%2C%20adding%20Zuckerberg%20was%20%26quot%3Btaking%20advantage%20of%20the%20moment%20to%20do%20what%20he%20thinks%20is%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-donald-trump-moderation-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtent%20moderation%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20scrutinized%20for%20years.%20Four%20years%20ago%2C%20Facebook%20banned%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20from%20the%20platform%20for%20policy%20violations%2C%20sparking%20the%20ire%20of%20Republicans%2C%20who%20have%20accused%20the%20site%20of%20silencing%20conservative%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20said%20he%20thought%20those%20complaints%20of%20bias%20were%20fair%20and%20that%20Meta%20could%20not%20find%20fact-checking%20organizations%20on%20the%20political%20right%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20as%20left-leaning%20ones.%20He%20said%20community%20notes%20on%20X%20have%20been%20more%20successful%20at%20getting%20people%20from%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20to%20contribute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%20Meta%20will%20take%20a%20different%20approach%20than%20X%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20relations%20with%20the%20brands%20that%20advertise%20on%20their%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20going%20out%20there%20denigrating%20our%20advertisers%20and%20putting%20them%20in%20terrible%20positions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20alluding%20to%20critical%20comments%20Musk%20has%20made%20about%20some%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-x-lawsuit-advertisers-boycott-antitrust-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX's%20advertisers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20X%20sued%20a%20group%20of%20advertisers%20in%20August%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20antitrust%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20said%20Facebook%20would%20maintain%20its%20brand%20safety%20tools%20that%20allow%20companies%20some%20control%20over%20the%20kinds%20of%20content%20their%20ads%20ap