3A%20%26quot%3BProbably%2C%20yeah.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20giant%20Meta%20on%20Tuesday%20slashed%20its%20content%20moderation%20policies%2C%20including%20ending%20its%20US%20fact-checking%20program%20on%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%2C%20in%20a%20major%20shift%20that%20conforms%20with%20the%20priorities%20of%20incoming%20president%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20fact-checkers%20(that)%20have%20just%20been%20too%20politically%20biased%20and%20have%20destroyed%20more%20trust%20than%20they've%20created%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20a%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Meta%20platforms%20including%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%2C%20%26quot%3Bwould%20use%20community%20notes%20similar%20to%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20starting%20in%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeta's%20surprise%20announcement%20echoed%20long-standing%20complaints%20made%20by%20Trump's%20Republican%20Party%20and%20X%20owner%20Elon%20Musk%20about%20fact-checking%2C%20which%20many%20conservatives%20see%20as%20censorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20argue%20that%20fact-checking%20programs%20disproportionately%20target%20right-wing%20voices%2C%20which%20has%20led%20to%20proposed%20laws%20in%20states%20like%20Florida%20and%20Texas%20to%20limit%20content%20moderation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20cool%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20posted%20on%20his%20X%20platform%20after%20the%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%2C%20in%20a%20nod%20to%20Trump's%20victory%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Brecent%20elections%20feel%20like%20a%20cultural%20tipping%20point%20towards%2C%20once%20again%2C%20prioritizing%20speech%26quot%3B%20over%20moderation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20came%20as%20the%2040-year-old%20tycoon%20has%20been%20making%20efforts%20to%20reconcile%20with%20Trump%20since%20his%20election%20in%20November%2C%20including%20donating%20one%20million%20dollars%20to%20his%20inauguration%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20been%20a%20harsh%20critic%20of%20Meta%20and%20Zuckerberg%20for%20years%2C%20accusing%20the%20company%20of%20bias%20against%20him%20and%20threatening%20to%20retaliate%20against%20the%20tech%20billionaire%20once%20back%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20reporters%20at%20his%20Mar-a-Lago%20estate%20in%20Florida%2C%20Trump%20when%20asked%20if%20he%20believed%20the%20move%20was%20a%20response%20to%20his%20threats%20against%20Zuckerberg%2C%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BProbably%2C%20yeah.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Republican%20was%20kicked%20off%20Facebook%20following%20the%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20attack%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20by%20his%20supporters%2C%20though%20the%20company%20restored%20his%20account%20in%20early%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EENDING%20'FACEBOOK%20JAIL'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%2C%20like%20several%20other%20tech%20leaders%2C%20has%20met%20with%20Trump%20at%20his%20Mar-a-Lago%20resort%20in%20Florida%20ahead%20of%20his%20January%2020%20inauguration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeta%20has%20made%20moves%20in%20recent%20days%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20please%20Trump's%20team%2C%20such%20as%20appointing%20former%20Republican%20official%20Joel%20Kaplan%20to%20head%20up%20public%20affairs%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20takes%20over%20from%20Nick%20Clegg%2C%20a%20former%20British%20deputy%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20also%20named%20Ultimate%20Fighting%20Championship%20(UFC)%20head%20Dana%20White%2C%20a%20close%20ally%20of%20Trump%2C%20to%20the%20Meta%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaplan%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20Tuesday%2C%20insisted%20the%20company's%20approach%20to%20content%20moderation%20had%20%26quot%3Bgone%20too%20far.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToo%20much%20harmless%20content%20gets%20censored%2C%20too%20many%20people%20find%20themselves%20wrongly%20locked%20up%20in%20'Facebook%20jail%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20overhaul%2C%20Meta%20said%20it%20will%20relocate%20its%20trust%20and%20safety%20teams%20from%20liberal%20California%20to%20more%20conservative%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20will%20help%20us%20build%20trust%20to%20do%20this%20work%20in%20places%20where%20there%20is%20less%20concern%20about%20the%20bias%20of%20our%20teams%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20also%20took%20a%20shot%20at%20the%20European%20Union%20%26quot%3Bthat%20has%20an%20ever%20increasing%20number%20of%20laws%20institutionalizing%20censorship%20and%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20build%20anything%20innovative%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remark%20referred%20to%20new%20laws%20in%20Europe%20that%20require%20Meta%20and%20other%20major%20platforms%20to%20maintain%20content%20moderation%20standards%20or%20risk%20hefty%20fines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20said%20that%20Meta%20would%20%26quot%3Bwork%20with%20President%20Trump%20to%20push%20back%20against%20foreign%20governments%20going%20after%20American%20companies%20to%20censor%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Meta%20announced%20it%20would%20reverse%20its%202021%20policy%20of%20reducing%20political%20content%20across%20its%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECOMMUNITY%20NOTES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENews%20agency%20AFP%20currently%20works%20in%2026%20languages%20with%20Facebook's%20fact-checking%20program%2C%20in%20which%20Facebook%20pays%20to%20use%20fact-checks%20from%20around%2080%20organizations%20globally%20on%20its%20platform%2C%20WhatsApp%20and%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20program%2C%20content%20rated%20%26quot%3Bfalse%26quot%3B%20is%20downgraded%20in%20news%20feeds%20so%20fewer%20people%20will%20see%20it%20and%20if%20someone%20tries%20to%20share%20that%20post%2C%20they%20are%20presented%20with%20